    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in the pay report about exit packages for ousted chief executives misstated a salary equivalent of the average severance in 2006. That average, $9 million, was equivalent to about 170 weeks of salary for each year, not each week, at the helm.</p>
